Anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's Demise Commemorated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- A meeting, seminar, lecture, photo exhibition and film shows were held from July 3 to 9 by the Peruvian Nationalist Party of the Andian Community, the Indian Working Women's Society for the Study of Juche Philosophy, in Goteborg City, Sweden, and at Agricultural College Named after Obiang in Malabo, Equatorial Guinea, and the Equatorial Guinea-DPRK Friendship Farm, the Kim Il Sung Institute of Agricultural Science and the Embroidery School of the International Solidarity Center in Guinea on the occasion of the 10th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's demise.
 On display in the venues of functions were photos showing the revolutionary activities and exploits of Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean films such as "1994 of Great Life" were screened at the film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretaries of the Peruvian Nationalist Party of the Andian Community and the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru in their speeches made at a meeting highly praised the immortal feats performed by Kim Il Sung for the Korean revolution and the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairperson of the Indian society said at a seminar that Kim Il Sung's ideological and theoretical exploits would be immortal with the era of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The international secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party Marxist-Leninist (R) in Sweden in a lecture looked back with deep emotion on the revolutionary life and immortal feats of Kim Il Sung and underscored the need to intensify the movement for solidarity with the Korean people in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director general of the Guinean institute at a lecture said that Kim Jong Il, regarding it as his lifelong mission to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche started by the President, has devoted his all to it, adding that the President's intention in his lifetime is being translated into a reality thanks to the intense loyalty and total dedication of Kim Jong Il to the President.

Anti-National Act of South Korean Military Authorities Flayed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity of south Korea on July 17 made public a statement titled "We denounce bellicose forces getting overheated in military attack."
 Recalling the announcement of the south Korean military authorities on July 14 that "a patrol craft of the north crossed the northern limit line" and they opened a warning fire in answer, the statement said it was unjustifiable for the military authorities to try still to rationalize the military counteraction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding the incident as a grave anti-national and bellicose act intended to scrap the agreement reached at the south-north military talks and create military tension, the statement continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Inter-Korean reconciliation and cooperation are already expanding to the military domain. The north is not our "enemy." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the fellow countrymen in the south and the north are now under obligation to observe the agreements on peace and unity and the army can never be an exception. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We demand that the military authorities not swim against the trend of the times toward the inter-Korean reconciliation, unity and peaceful reunification.

Anniversary of Cuban People's July 26 Armed Uprising Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held here Thursday on the occasion of the 51st anniversary of the Cuban people's July 26 Armed Uprising.
 Present there on invitation were Cuban Ambassador to the DPRK Esteban Lobaina Romero and staff members of the embassy here.
  Also present were Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education who is chairman of the DPRK-Cuba Solidarity Committee, Kim Yong Do, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, officials concerned and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Speeches were made at the meeting that started with the playing of the national anthems of Cuba and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was followed by a film show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants appreciated the Korean feature film "He Was Senior Colonel".

8th National Exhibition of Invention and New Technology Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- The 8th National Exhibition of Invention and New Technology opened at the Three-Revolution Exhibition Thursday.
 On display in the form of real thing, model, video recording, diagram and so forth are over 1,000 pieces of invention and new technology achieved by scientists, technicians, officials and working people across the country in their efforts to develop the nation's science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While the exhibition is open there will be a work for the dissemination and generalization of worthy items of invention and new technology in the form of scientific and technological presentation, short course, etc. and diverse information services including the introduction of exhibits through information service networks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the opening ceremony were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Kim Sung Hyon, minister of Metal and Machine-Building Industries, Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, officials concerned, scientists, technicians, inventors and working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pyon Yong Rip, president of the Academy of Sciences, addressing the opening ceremony, said all the officials, scientists, technicians and inventors should make substantial contributions to making a breakthrough on the economic and scientific front by devoting all their energy and wisdom to the development of the nation's science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the opening ceremony, the participants went round the exhibition hall.

U.S. Urged to Pay for Blood Shed by Koreans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson Friday carries a signed commentary as regards the recent discovery of a U.S. document dealing with its forces' killing of civilians in cold blood in the waters off Phohang, North Kyongsang Province during the Korean war.
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recently disclosed mass killing of civilians is just a tip of iceberg of the monstrous massacres committed by the U.S. imperialists in various parts of Korea during the Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was widely known that they massacred innocent civilians in cold blood everywhere after igniting a war against the DPRK in the 1950s.The piled up dead bodies of the south Koreans killed by the U.S. imperialists until now would be as high as a mountain and the blood shed by them fill a reservoir. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As facts prove, the U.S. troops in south Korea are neither "friends" of the south Korean people nor "apostles of peace." They serve as a lever backing the U.S. colonial rule over it with arms and a frontline shock force for a war against the north. The U.S. imperialists' introduction of over 10 F-117 Stealth bombers to south Korea and their development of missiles capable of underground penetration are aimed at starting a new war on the Korean peninsula. It is as clear as noonday that the outbreak of another war in Korea would cause such massacre of civilians as what happened in Rogun-ri and Phohang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation will launch a nationwide struggle against the U.S. to force it to pay for the blood shed by the innocent Koreans thousand times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists should apologize to the Korean nation for the monstrous crimes committed so far and immediately withdraw their forces from south Korea as early as possible.

Action Taken to Disallow Pyongyang Visit of Ngo Delegation under�@Fire in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly held a regular meeting of its central steering committee on July 17 at which it released a special statement accusing the south Korean authorities of disallowing the Pyongyang visit by a non-governmental delegation of south Korea to participate in functions to commemorate the tenth anniversary of the demise of President Kim Il Sung.
 The statement sternly chided the Ministry of Unification for disallowing the Pyongyang visit of personages of a non-governmental organization including Presbyter Pak Yong Gil, widow of Rev. Mun Ik Hwan, to participate in the above-said functions. Such action was an anachronistic anti-reunification behavior reminiscent of the rash action taken against those south Koreans who wished to mourn the death of the President in 1994 and an unethical action of ignoring even the ancestral good manners and customs and elemental human morality, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government should immediately allow the Pyongyang visit by the non-governmental delegation, though belatedly. And the forces for the reunification movement should carry on their struggle till its visit has been realized and thus force the government to completely change its attitude toward the non-governmental exchanges. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next year is a significant year which will mark the fifth anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, the statement said, calling upon all the people to draw a lesson from the incident and make every possible effort to put the non-governmental exchanges on a new higher stage.
